The President and Senior Administration officials met with influential Hispanics to discuss the importance of fixing the broken immigration system. The President expressed disappointment in the lack of Congressional action on immigration reform and the failure of the DREAM Act to pass. He emphasized the need to educate talented individuals and not expel them from the country. The President reiterated his commitment to comprehensive immigration reform that strengthens security and restores accountability. He noted that legislative action is necessary to fix the broken system. The President urged meeting participants to help elevate the debate and reach out in their unique capacities to forge partnerships. There was agreement that more voices are needed to change the tone of the debate. The President will continue to work towards bipartisan consensus and lead a civil debate on the issue. Prior to the meeting, senior Administration officials also briefed participants on important issues such as the economy and education.